Dear Kyungnam Jeon,

Overlapping confidence intervals for two subgroups does not mean that 
there is no significant p-value for the subgroup difference. See, for 
example, 
http://blog.minitab.com/blog/real-world-quality-improvement/common-statistical-mistakes-you-should-avoid 
.

Best wishes,
Guido

