Yes, b3 = -.0511 is the main effect of the 'tester' factor. Since there is no interaction, the effect is the same for all three levels of the 'weeks' factor, so it is not just the simple effect for the 'none' level, but also for the 'some' and 'high' levels. Look at the line plot again -- it does not matter at which level of 'weeks' you look, the b3 = -.0511 effect is always the same.

Best,
Wolfgang

